      <h1 class="w3-text-teal">Shelter</h1>
      <p>Shelters provide protection from the elements. Shelters usually consist of tents or tarps. A tent is a fully enclosed shelter that protects from weather and bugs. A tarp is an exposed shelter that offers protection from weather but not bugs. <br><br>Tents come in single wall and double wall. Double wall tents have an external rain proof layer and an internal bug proof layer. The separate layers prevent condensation from forming on the inside of the tent. Double walls provide very good rain protection and ventilation.  Single wall tents only have one layer that doubles as bug and weather protection. Single wall tents can be much lighter than a double wall tent, but the weight reduction comes at a a price. Condensation and breathability are significantly worse in a single wall tent. <br><br> Tarps are the lightest option. They can provide excellent weather protection, but require skill to properly pitch. A single tarp can be pitched many different ways depending on the site. Tarps do not offer bug protection and may be impractical in heavy mosquito areas.  </p>
    </div>
