      <h1 class="w3-text-teal">Sleeping System</h1>
      <p>A sleeping system usually consist of a sleeping bag/quilt and a sleeping pad (we won't get into hammocks). <br> <br>
      A sleeping quilt is similar to a sleeping bag, but without out a back(the part you lay on). This cuts down on weight and results in sleeping quilts be slightly lighter than sleeping bags. Whether you choose a sleeping quilt or bag, you the bag should be made with a synthetic shell and down insulation. Ultralight sleeping bags/quilts should weigh around two pounds. <br><br> Sleeping pads insulate you from the cold hard ground. There are three types: air pads, self inflating pads, and closed-cell foam pads. Air pads can be inflated using breath and offer the most comfort, but are prone to puncture. Self-inflating pads are made of an inflatable shell with foam inside the shell. These don't require breath to inflate, but come with a weight penalty. Closed-cell foam pads are made of foam filled with tiny closed air cells. They are very durable, but offer less cushon. Ultralight sleeping pads should weigh around one pound.  </p>
    </div>
    <div class="w3-third w3-container">
