      <h1 class="w3-text-teal">Backpack</h1>
      <p>A good backpack should distribute weight between your shoulders and hips allowing all day hiking without irritation. There are three types of backpacks: internal frame, frameless, and external frame. <br><br>Internal frame backpacks have frames made from aluminum or carbon fiber inside the backpack. A frame gives the pack structure allowing the pack weight to be distributed to the hips. The adds comfort but comes at a weight penalty. A good internal framed backpack should weigh around 3 pounds. <br><br>Frameless pack have no rigid structural components. The packs structure is formed through proper packing and compression. Frameless packs are by far the lightest pack option, but require a low pack weight and good packing. Frameless packs should not be used if your pack weight ever exceeds 20 pounds. A good frameless backpack should weigh around 1 pound.<br><br>External frames have tubular aluminum frames outside of the pack fabric. They are the heaviest and are generally considered to be outdated. </p>
